COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1094, L.D. 1653
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, adds persons who have
33 received an associate degree or a credential to those who are potentially eligible for the
44 Maine Credentialed Workforce Program established in the bill and clarifies that to be
55 eligible for the program an applicant must have outstanding student loan debt or eligible
66 student loans. The amendment also provides that an applicant must have received the
77 applicant's degree or credential within 5 years of the date of application, rather than within
88 2 years as proposed in the bill.
